277
00:13:30,047 --> 00:13:33,570
And the key things about this is, about this art,

278
00:13:33,970 --> 00:13:35,471
first of all, it's very distinctive,

279
00:13:35,851 --> 00:13:39,214
people use this art style now for Twitter avatars

280
00:13:39,254 --> 00:13:41,035
or Steam avatars to identify themselves

281
00:13:41,095 --> 00:13:42,256
as cultist-simulated players.

282
00:13:42,716 --> 00:13:43,917
And everybody who's seen it knows it.

283
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:48,002
It's also really cheap to produce in mass quantities.

284
00:13:48,042 --> 00:13:50,764
You can whack out several of these in a day quite easily,

285
00:13:50,884 --> 00:13:52,645
which when you have our budgets is vitally important.

286
00:13:54,606 --> 00:13:56,748
So that's one good way into being distinctive.

287
00:13:56,808 --> 00:13:58,389
Here's another one, a much more general one.

288
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:00,030
Genre.

289
00:14:01,651 --> 00:14:04,553
Genre is a tool for communication and a tool for marketing.

290
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:07,875
If I say that I'm making a side scrolling to be at the RPG,

291
00:14:07,915 --> 00:14:10,517
you immediately know a lot of what I'm trying to do.

292
00:14:10,757 --> 00:14:12,739
And you immediately have some idea

293
00:14:12,779 --> 00:14:14,080
if you're likely to like it or not.

294
00:14:15,364 --> 00:14:21,474
But, so people will tell you that you should find a genre,

295
00:14:21,494 --> 00:14:23,858
that you should fit your game into the places

296
00:14:23,878 --> 00:14:25,220
where other people like those genres,

297
00:14:25,821 --> 00:14:27,724
you should try to establish commonalities based on that.

298
00:14:27,764 --> 00:14:29,266
And that all can be good advice.

299
00:14:30,532 --> 00:14:32,433
But there is another route, and the other route is

300
00:14:32,853 --> 00:14:34,735
explicitly to eschew genre.

301
00:14:35,395 --> 00:14:36,757
And even if you explicitly eschew genre,

302
00:14:36,797 --> 00:14:38,458
we're still talking about cultist simulator

303
00:14:38,478 --> 00:14:41,780
being sort of a simulation, or sort of a card game,

304
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,762
or sort of a rogue-like, or sort of a horror game,

305
00:14:44,262 --> 00:14:45,623
or try to get to those audiences.

306
00:14:46,764 --> 00:14:49,126
But if you identify yourself firmly with a genre,

307
00:14:49,466 --> 00:14:52,689
it's very hard to stand out from all the other things

308
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:54,170
that are in that genre.

309
00:14:54,591 --> 00:14:56,652
So eschewing genre is one way to be distinctive.

310
00:14:58,527 --> 00:15:01,508
Divisiveness, right, those of a nervous disposition

