355
00:17:05,077 --> 00:17:07,378
And the reason that many of you recognize this image

356
00:17:07,879 --> 00:17:08,799
is that it went viral.

357
00:17:10,085 --> 00:17:13,626
because everybody who saw the dress as blue and black

358
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:16,427
could not believe what the white and gold folks

359
00:17:16,447 --> 00:17:17,888
were on about and they wanted to explain

360
00:17:17,908 --> 00:17:18,968
to each other why they're wrong.

361
00:17:20,369 --> 00:17:24,391
And if you are an indie dev trying to build a community,

362
00:17:25,891 --> 00:17:28,472
yes, the thing about communities,

363
00:17:29,753 --> 00:17:32,354
and this leads into the dark arts, honestly,

364
00:17:32,914 --> 00:17:35,555
is that a community is defined by other people

365
00:17:35,595 --> 00:17:36,876
not being part of that community.

366
00:17:37,725 --> 00:17:40,406
Any community that doesn't have an edge is the human race.

367
00:17:42,627 --> 00:17:45,949
And the thing about a community

368
00:17:45,969 --> 00:17:47,750
that has strongly defined boundaries

369
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:50,291
is it feels very strongly about its identity.

370
00:17:51,752 --> 00:17:54,514
Now, in the age of Brexit and Trump

371
00:17:54,614 --> 00:17:56,535
and the polarization of politics in the UK

372
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:57,675
and the US and elsewhere,

373
00:17:57,695 --> 00:18:01,517
this is gonna evoke some alarming thoughts.

374
00:18:01,978 --> 00:18:03,859
So you must only use this power for good.

375
00:18:04,239 --> 00:18:05,079
But the thing is,

376
00:18:06,007 --> 00:18:12,216
In the case of Cultist Simulator, in the case of games with thoughtful, non-toxic communities,

377
00:18:12,356 --> 00:18:16,462
often this power is usable for good. I said earlier that there are three kinds of response

378
00:18:16,502 --> 00:18:21,789
to Cultist usually. Love it, don't get it, nearly love it but hate it.

379
00:18:23,736 --> 00:18:27,038
And very, very often, I'll jump into the Steam forums.

380
00:18:27,078 --> 00:18:29,020
There's Steam forums in all places.

381
00:18:29,481 --> 00:18:31,763
And I'll see a thread that begins by somebody saying,

382
00:18:31,823 --> 00:18:33,624
I don't get this game at all.

383
00:18:34,725 --> 00:18:36,527
I put cards in slots and words happen.

384
00:18:37,588 --> 00:18:40,310
And occasionally, it's a reasonable summation

385
00:18:40,330 --> 00:18:41,011
of the game, honestly.

386
00:18:41,351 --> 00:18:44,514
But occasionally, people will come in and go,

387
00:18:44,594 --> 00:18:45,515
lol, sucks to be you.

388
00:18:45,675 --> 00:18:46,716
This game is for smart people.

389
00:18:47,176 --> 00:18:48,297
But that doesn't often happen.

390
00:18:49,313 --> 00:18:52,336
fortunately, what very often happens,

391
00:18:52,516 --> 00:18:54,918
heartwarmingly so, is the thread will fill up

392
00:18:55,058 --> 00:18:57,501
with people saying, yeah, it's a tough one, this.

393
00:18:59,082 --> 00:19:00,724
Where particularly are you running into problems?

394
00:19:01,264 --> 00:19:02,205
Have you tried this?

395
00:19:02,786 --> 00:19:04,387
This is how we fix the problem you're talking about.

396
00:19:04,928 --> 00:19:06,409
Read everything really carefully.

397
00:19:06,489 --> 00:19:08,951
No, seriously, read everything really carefully.

398
00:19:08,971 --> 00:19:09,752
It all means something.

399
