1134
00:54:02,473 --> 00:54:05,375
that decision was made and how it might have required you

1135
00:54:05,415 --> 00:54:08,556
to revisit some of the mechanics or changes or if at all.

1136
00:54:09,781 --> 00:54:13,344
Excellent question, and it was, when in the design process

1137
00:54:13,364 --> 00:54:14,926
did we decide not to put a tutorial in?

1138
00:54:15,106 --> 00:54:16,467
So I decided this very early.

1139
00:54:16,487 --> 00:54:18,509
And one thing I didn't touch on in the talk,

1140
00:54:18,629 --> 00:54:20,471
because it's more a design talk than a production talk,

1141
00:54:21,032 --> 00:54:24,034
is that if you leave something like a tutorial out, well done,

1142
00:54:24,135 --> 00:54:28,158
you've saved 10K off your budget, which is a bonus.

1143
00:54:28,479 --> 00:54:29,780
So that was the intention from the start.

1144
00:54:29,900 --> 00:54:33,003
But about two months before launch, my co-founder,

1145
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:36,663
and our publisher both started to get very nervous about it

1146
00:54:37,083 --> 00:54:40,346
because a lot of people would start playing the game casually and they'd just bounce off it.

1147
00:54:41,287 --> 00:54:46,312
And when we took it to an event a lot of people said I keep putting the cards in the slots and

1148
00:54:46,352 --> 00:54:51,397
nothing happens. And Lottie and Humble both said

1149
00:54:52,397 --> 00:54:54,218
Maybe we should consider putting a tutorial in.

1150
00:54:54,358 --> 00:54:55,779
And I said, no, vision.

1151
00:54:56,199 --> 00:54:59,681
And more seriously, if we start telling people

1152
00:54:59,722 --> 00:55:02,163
what they can do early on, they won't experiment.

1153
00:55:02,183 --> 00:55:03,524
They'll expect to have their hand held later

1154
00:55:03,564 --> 00:55:04,425
and it won't be as interesting.

1155
00:55:06,868 --> 00:55:10,412
And so often when you've got a design tension like that,

1156
00:55:10,993 --> 00:55:13,095
it was resolved by finding a third way, which

1157
00:55:13,115 --> 00:55:15,798
was to radically limit the number of cards

1158
00:55:15,818 --> 00:55:17,140
you could put in particular slots.

1159
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:18,842
It used to be you could put any kind of card

1160
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:19,623
in any kind of slot.

1161
00:55:19,643 --> 00:55:22,186
And we said, no, the only things that can go in the work slot

1162
00:55:22,366 --> 00:55:23,267
are abilities.

1163
00:55:24,148 --> 00:55:29,591
dobs right and that meant that nearly every combination the game that's possible has some

1164
00:55:29,671 --> 00:55:33,814
sort of effect so the player doesn't feel they're banging on the wall and listening for an answer

1165
00:55:33,854 --> 00:55:38,357
they feel they're there they always get a response the game is having a conversation with them so

1166
00:55:38,377 --> 00:55:38,917
that's the answer to that.

