1176
00:55:59,222 --> 00:56:00,263
something you would do differently

1177
00:56:00,343 --> 00:56:02,964
is try to include more polish

1178
00:56:03,245 --> 00:56:04,906
or things like a tutorial maybe.

1179
00:56:05,766 --> 00:56:07,567
What is the process for determining

1180
00:56:07,808 --> 00:56:08,888
when you're done with the game?

1181
00:56:09,148 --> 00:56:10,629
Like when it's going to be released?

1182
00:56:10,689 --> 00:56:12,571
Is it purely budgetary concerns?

1183
00:56:12,591 --> 00:56:13,571
Like it has to come out now?

1184
00:56:13,992 --> 00:56:17,173
continue as a company or what is it?

1185
00:56:17,753 --> 00:56:21,434
So another excellent question is how do we decide

1186
00:56:21,474 --> 00:56:23,194
when we're gonna finish production

1187
00:56:23,234 --> 00:56:24,795
on these very short timescale games?

1188
00:56:26,535 --> 00:56:31,717
And the answer is to play chicken with deadlines, I think.

1189
00:56:32,457 --> 00:56:35,538
I'm a big believer in deadlines promoting ingenuity.

1190
00:56:35,958 --> 00:56:36,958
I take them seriously.

1191
00:56:36,978 --> 00:56:41,280
And when we took the game to events early on,

1192
00:56:41,300 --> 00:56:43,280
we actually had our deadline printed on the banner.

1193
00:56:44,321 --> 00:56:48,884
I said that it would be... we did the Kickstarter in September, I'd done three months production

1194
00:56:48,924 --> 00:56:54,608
privacy, released in May and we said 31st May was the deadline and people came up to us and said

1195
00:56:54,628 --> 00:56:59,292
that's a bold choice, printing your deadline on there, but it holds us to account. We didn't

1196
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:03,034
crunch, we worked a bit of overtime towards the end and we got ratty with each other,

1197
00:57:03,455 --> 00:57:06,797
but we just cut like crazy. In terms of polish...

1198
00:57:09,279 --> 00:57:12,560
Next time I think we would do, this is what we discussed,

1199
00:57:12,780 --> 00:57:15,081
fewer features and a bit more UI work.

1200
00:57:15,121 --> 00:57:16,762
I think that's what would have made the difference,

1201
00:57:16,862 --> 00:57:17,862
is prioritization.

1202
00:57:19,403 --> 00:57:22,224
Working to tough deadlines also really sharpens

1203
00:57:22,244 --> 00:57:23,284
your estimation skills.

1204
00:57:23,324 --> 00:57:24,785
It's much easier to work to deadlines

1205
00:57:24,865 --> 00:57:25,925
once you've worked to deadlines.

1206
00:57:26,865 --> 00:57:29,126
But all that said, next time we're thinking about

1207
00:57:29,146 --> 00:57:31,567
is keeping a sort of a bucket of undefined time

1208
00:57:32,247 --> 00:57:34,388
that Lottie will be the guardian of rather than me,

1209
00:57:34,408 --> 00:57:36,609
but I have to make the case for spending time on,

1210
00:57:36,629 --> 00:57:37,489
